(2, 'agreement', 'USERS AGREEMENT Lt', 'USERS AGREEMENT', 'USERS AGREEMENT Ru', 'USERS AGREEMENT Lt', 'USERS AGREEMENT', 'USERS AGREEMENT Ru', '<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">1. Introduction Lt</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">1.1. This Privacy Policy (hereinafter the Policy) applies to all information about what our bank may receive about the User while using our banking system.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">1.2. The use of the Bank’s systems by the User means the User’s absolute agreement with this Offer Policy and the conditions specified therein for the processing of his personal information, identification process and other actions related to the bank account; In case of disagreement with these conditions, the user should refrain from using Avrora Capital Bank.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">2. Terms and definitions</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.1. Bank - Interregional Commercial Bank for the Development of Communications and Informatics. Short name - Avrora Capital Bank.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.2. Client - an individual who has entered into an agreement with the Banking Services Bank.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.3. Personal data processing (processing) - any action (operation) or a set of actions (operations) is carried out using automation tools or without using such tools with personal data, including collection, recording, systematization, accumulation, storage, updating (updating, changing), extraction, use, transfer (distribution, provision, access), depersonalization, blocking, deletion, destruction of personal data (if this entails a negative impact on the reputation of our bank, s in the case of a request protectors).</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.4. Personal data - any data related to a person is directly or indirectly determined or determined by an individual (and the subject of personal data).</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.5. Personal information - any information that the User directly or indirectly provides about himself in the process of using Payments Land systems, including personal information.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.6. The user is a person using BankSystems \" Avrora Capital Bank \". The user may be a customer of the Bank.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.7. Avrora Capital Bank systems include: Avrora Capital Bank Internet banking system (including Mobile Banking subsystems), SMS banking and SMS-Info system, contact center, ATMs, self-service terminals.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">3. User Personal Information</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.1. Users who are customers of the Bank transfer personal data of the Bank on the basis of agreements concluded with the Bank. The processing of such data is determined by the relevant contracts.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.2. Personal data of clients whose processing is not determined by the relevant contracts is processed in accordance with this policy.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.3. Personal Information Non-client users are processed in accordance with this policy.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.4. As part of this policy, the following types of information are processed:</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.4.1. Information that user transfers are independent of each other during the use of the Avrora Capital Bank System, including personal data (for example, when filling out a form, application). The user independently decides on the transfer of information to the bank, including the refusal to transmit information;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.4.2. Information is automatically transmitted to the Bank in the process of using the “Avrora Capital Bank” system, including IP addresses, data from cookies, device information and the user\'s browser, time of an active session / connection to the system, etc. In Generally, the user can not control the transmission of information of this type, which limits the transmission of information of this type can disrupt the functioning of the system.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.5. Information about the location of the User is automatically transmitted to the Bank of the user\'s device. The user can control the transfer of such information by changing the settings of his device.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.6. with the exception of cases of verification of customers on the basis and in the manner prescribed by agreements concluded with customers, the Bank verifies the authenticity of personal information provided by users</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.7. When processing the User’s personal data, the Bank is guided by Federal Law No. 152-ФЗ dated July 27, 2006 “On Personal Data”.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.8. The verification procedure includes replenishing the bank account of our system by the number of a virtual bank card issued in our system for identifying individuals online or at the bank\'s office for legal entities. The recharge amount depends on the serial number in our banking system and can be valued from 0.01 to $ 1500.00.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.9. The amount is set after registering your account in the database of our bank (this procedure takes up to 24 hours or after the first incoming transaction in excess of $ 100).</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.10. In some cases, the monitoring system may request an additional level of verification, confirmation of the relevance of a bank card, which includes recharge to the same amount of identification within two hours from the receipt of the recharge for identification. Also note that for customers with the Russian Federation, when transferring directly from the territories of the CIS countries, it is necessary to inform the Administrator before replenishment in order to replenish the past moderation, if you do not inform before replenishment, the funds arrive as a regular transfer, a warning for identification is compulsory.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">3.11. The time for user identification in the absence of incoming transactions is limited to 72 hours, when funds are credited to the account in excess of $ 100, the time is limited to 00:00 of the current day, if more than 6 hours are left until the end of the current day, in other cases it is limited to 12: 00 days of the next calendar day in the time zone of Moscow.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4. The goals of collecting and processing personal information of users to combat money laundering and legalization of income</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.1. The Bank processes only the processing of personal information necessary to provide services to the User.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.2. The user\'s personal information may be used by the Bank for the following purposes:</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.2.1. Customer Identification;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.2.2. Providing personalized services for the user;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.2.3. Communication with the user, including sending notifications, requests and information regarding the use of Avrora Capital Bank systems, as well as processing requests, confirmations and orders of the User;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.2.4. Improving the quality of service, ease of use, development of new services;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.2.5. Conducting statistical and other studies based on anonymized data, including targeting advertising materials. 5. Collection and use of information that is not personal.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.3. In case of blocking the account for exceeding the limit for withdrawing funds, you must perform the unlocking procedure by replenishing the account in the amount of 10,000.00 rubles (for Russian citizens) for citizens of other countries the amount is equivalent to 150 Euro, the unlocking procedure is limited to 00:00 Moscow time on the current day , in the absence of timely unlocking, you can extend the time by depositing a symbolic amount into your account equal to 2001 rubles for citizens of the Russian Federation or 28.00 Euro, in other cases access to the account will be completely limited without the possibility of distance onnoy unlock. With the ability to unlock only through a personal visit to the office of our bank.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.3.1. The amount to unlock for exceeding the limit on withdrawal of funds (clause 8.2.) Is set at 10001.00 rubles for citizens of the Russian Federation, or 150.00 Euro for citizens of other countries. rubles.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.3.2. In case of blocking for other reasons, the unlocking must be done directly at our head office in our main and only office in the UK</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">4.3.3. In the event of an account lockout, the system may request a re-identification</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">5.1. The bank can process such information as a unique identifier for the device, in the URL of the communication channel source, the time zone in which the user is located. The purpose of this processing is to study the needs of users in order to offer them the most suitable products and services.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">5.2. The Bank may process information about user actions when using our system. This information is used to optimize the Bank name system.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">5.3. If information that is not Personal is combined with personal information, the combined information is considered Personal until it merges.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">6. Collection and use of information related to the address</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">6.1. In order to provide location-based services, the Bank may collect real-time data on the geographical location of a user\'s computer or mobile device. The location can use GPS, Bluetooth, IP address and other technologies to determine the exact or approximate location of a computer or mobile device. Location data is collected anonymously in a form that does not allow you to identify the user. Such data is not personal information.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">6.2. In some cases, the user may be asked to explicitly determine his location.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">6.3. When combining information about the location of the User with his personal information, the combined information is considered Personal as long as it remains merged.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">6.4. The location of users is used by the Bank to provide and improve products and services that use location data.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">7. Conditions for transferring personal information to third parties</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1. The Bank is entitled to transfer user personal information to third parties in the following cases:</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1.1. The user has expressed his consent to such actions;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1.2. Transfer is necessary to complete the order of the User;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1.3. In order to ensure the possibility of protecting the rights and legitimate interests of the Bank in cases where the Bank has reasonable grounds to believe that the User violates the terms of this policy, agreements concluded with the Bank and / or the requirements of European law.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">7. Conditions for transferring personal information to third parties</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1. The Bank is entitled to transfer user personal information to third parties in the following cases:</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1.1. The user has expressed his consent to such actions;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1.2. Transfer is necessary to complete the order of the User;</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">7.1.3. In order to ensure the possibility of protecting the rights and legitimate interests of the Bank in cases where the Bank has reasonable grounds to believe that the User violates the terms of this policy, agreements concluded with the Bank and / or the requirements of European law.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">8. Protection of user personal information</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">8.1. The Bank takes the necessary and sufficient organizational and technical measures to protect the User of personal information from unauthorized or accidental access, destruction, alteration, blocking, copying, distribution, as well as from other illegal actions of third parties with him.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">8.2. Withdrawal limits.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">8.2.1. The limitation of outgoing operations of accounts at that time is the equivalent of 1200.00 Euro per 1 transaction. The daily limit is 24,000.00 Euro. (Maximum 20 transactions) The monthly limit is 150,000.00 euros. If this limit is exceeded, the Avrora Capital Bank control system sets the account in a restricted mode. (The procedure for removing the limitation is clause 4.3.)</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">9. Change in privacy policy</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">9.1. The Bank has the right to unilaterally change this policy. The new version of the Policy comes into force from the moment it is posted on the Bank\'s website at: Essential-invest unless otherwise provided by the new version of the Policy.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">10. In some cases, the system may require the payment of VAT in international transfers.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">10.1. The amount of VAT is equal to 13% to 18% of the balance. The new version of the Policy comes into force from the moment it is posted on the Bank\'s website at: Avrora Capital Bank, unless otherwise provided by the new version of the Policy.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">11. I also agree to receive SMS and email notifications about the actions on the account from registration in the system until the termination of this agreement in writing.</p>\r\n				</div>', '<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">1. Introduction</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">1.1. This Privacy Policy (hereinafter the Policy) applies to all information about what our bank may receive about the User while using our banking system.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">1.2. The use of the Bank’s systems by the User means the User’s absolute agreement with this Offer Policy and the conditions specified therein for the processing of his personal information, identification process and other actions related to the bank account; In case of disagreement with these conditions, the user should refrain from using Avrora Capital Bank.</p>\r\n				</div>\r\n\r\n				<div class=\"block-info\">\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__title\">2. Terms and definitions</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.1. Bank - Interregional Commercial Bank for the Development of Communications and Informatics. Short name - Avrora Capital Bank.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"block-info__text\">2.2. Client - an individual who has entered into an agreement with the Banking Services Bank.</p>\r\n					<p class=\"